A vintage-style illustration of an air traffic control tower at dusk, with a small propeller airplane circling nearby. Inside the tower's glowing windows, silhouettes of controllers work at their stations. Below, a complex web of golden telegraph wires and pneumatic tubes connects the tower to a grand art deco filing cabinet building, with small illuminated document capsules traveling through the transparent tubes in both directions. The scene has warm sepia tones with touches of amber and copper, reminiscent of 1940s aviation posters. Paper airplanes made of official-looking documents float in organized patterns around the tower, each trailing a thin golden thread back to their origin point, creating an elegant visual metaphor of tracked communication loops against a dusky purple and orange sky.
